1.defect Status: Reopened- If a tester finds the fix isn't working, they'll change the status to "Reopened".
Indicates the defect wasn't fixed and needs further work.
Notifies the developer to re-examine and re-fix the issue.
 Helps track defects that require additional attention.
 Ensures the defect is re-addressed and re-tested.
 Typically, the tester updates the status.
Triggers re-notification to the developer.
 Allows for re-prioritization and re-allocation of resources.
 Maintains transparency and visibility.
 Ensures defect is fully resolved before closure.
